The paper applies deep learning to the problem of liquid perception and reasoning, which is a task relevant to robotics and computer vision. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses fully-convolutional deep neural networks, which are a type of artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different models, indicating that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for LSTM-based neural networks to enable robots to handle liquids using closed-loop controllers, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category.
